  "slug": "threshold-aware-model",
  "title": "If Maia-2's unified model beats population-specific models at move prediction because it learns the skill gradient, could a threshold-aware unified model (a discontinuity detector on the skill embedding) recover the population-specific model's advantage for thresholded concepts — or does the smoothing that helps smooth concepts inevitably blur the thresholds?",
